// As of Prompt007, the canonical, emulator-validated, production-oriented
// security rules live in `firestore.rules` (same directory). That file is
// the single source of truth and the one you deploy.
//
// This `.example` file is kept only as a historical pointer so older docs
// and links do not break. It intentionally contains NO rules of its own to
// avoid drift between two copies.
//
// To review the rules:      open firestore.rules
// To validate locally:      npm run test:rules   (Firebase Emulator)
// To deploy (after review):  firebase deploy --only firestore:rules
